data.text: Hehe! Ur cat has awesome faces! And her major icon of those faces is her eyes! So adorable!
Cute! Looks just like my cat! Check my gallery

@tyrshand It derives from the word 'comel', which means 'cute' in my native language, Bahasa Melayu (Malay). My 10 year old sister used to pronounce 'comel' as 'cho-me-ya' back when she was about 2. Chomeya came into our lives in July 2010- We found her loitering outside our home as a kitten, approximately about 4 months old, looking rather cold, hungry and scrawny, and we then decided to take her in that very night. We didn't know what to name her the next day and instead of going with the ridiculous names my little sister came up with, I decided to call her Chomeya cause I thought it was fitting for a cute little kitten. :) Sorry for this rather long-winded story. Thanks for asking!

Loves cats expressions, right now my cats is smiling, when he's scared he has his ears back, when he is tired his eyes are barely closed and he makes his tummy poke out. I like discovering patterns with my 2 kitties in their mood! My other cat always likes to play so she always gets wide eyes and had her fluff in her neck pooched... My old cat, that was a tabby, had some faces that chomeya had! Super cute! Love ur fotos! Bye
